<item>
            <title>[HBASE-15641] Shell &quot;alter&quot; should do a single modifyTable operation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15641</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When performing an &quot;alter&quot; on multiple column families in a table, then shell will perform a separate &lt;tt&gt;Admin.modifyColumn()&lt;/tt&gt; call for each column family being modified, with all of the table regions being bulk-reopened each time.  It would be much better to simply apply all the changes to the table descriptor, then do a single call to &lt;tt&gt;Admin.modifyTable()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
